         Violent you are way understating it out of objectivity perhaps.  Look guys.  No matter how you spin it, this change was so overpowering for caster mobs that it completely unbalances the game.  Alan's poor attempt at minimizing the impact is laughable.  Since when is it fair that mobs 10 or more levels below you will be owning you.</P><P>The thing you all are completely missing is the fact that there DOES NOT have to be a FAIRNESS balance between caster npcs and pcs.  PCs pay to play the game and have fun.  NPCs are computer generated animations controlled by a computer.  There is no NEED to make them nuke better.  The game is hard enough as it is for PCs and in many respects very aggravating, monotnous and difficult.  We are not talking about balancing between different PC classes that have legitimate gripes and pocketbooks that VI wants into.  I could see if the caster mobs were triviliazed.  They are not (mana, massive hp, big melee).  Unless you are prepared to decrease many of their advantages they recieved because they were NOT smarter before, you have killed the game with caster mobs.</P><P>Alan appears almost as if he is personifying the npc casters as a way to make the "fair" argument.  Alan, have you ever played the game?  My god.  Anyone remember how hard it is to take Orc Hill (untwinked jerkos) at level 4.  Those shamans were bad enough and there are plenty of wipeouts.  WTF will you do now.  Peeps are just learning the game at the level.  Are you now going to require raid style actions for 4th levels?</P><P>53rd Heretic of Misty Knight (Tholluxe Paels)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
