        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <BR>Wow, I thought the first comment was stupid but this one is downright idiotic... to the point of being offensive. The most obvious being this doesn't need "case-by-case" modifications it needs an answer to the burning questions of what the f*** where you thinking? dropping a huge change into the game, with seemingly no concern or consideration for game balance, is just... disappointing.</P><P>Caster mobs, especially in dungeons with anything less than an optimal group, where already plenty dangerous. If you double their power with no increase in reward, if you make player death quick and arbitrary and party wipes far more common it doesn't make for a better game....or were the NPC's threatening to go to SWG or something?</P><P>And as for "pick the time and the party" as a PC advantage. Heh, wakey, wakey. Sometimes we have these advantages. But in most dungeons your lucky to find a full group, let alone a balanced one. And given pathing and agro it is certain you will, sooner or later, have a bad pull. A bad pull which is now far worse.</P><P>Grats though. You really have made dungeons no-go area's. If there's spell casters in them, and many of them are caster heavy, forget going in unless they're deep green and non agro or you have a well quipped and balanced party. No chanter to do crowd control? forget it. No one to buff resists? forget it. No tank to absorb the spells and cleric to rez when the rogue drops in a single cast? forget it. In other words the risk in this game, unless you have complete control of the area, has had a huge, and uncalled for, escalation.</P><P>The only safe way to get xp is.... have a full group, an open area so you can pick your target and avoid adds, and a dominance of melee mobs. Grats, you've made anything other than xp grinding dangerous and unrewarding.</P><P>dumb, dumb move... and it scares me that you thought anyone but the terminal bored twinkie would think it a good idea.</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_